input_str: Both Buddhism and gnosticism (gnosticism as a typological category) see our phenomenal world as a deception (maya) insofar as it is not what it appears to be. Worse still, at bottom, it only gives suffering to its subjects who cling to it. In the final analysis, nothing is signified by the phenomenal world except its nothingness as an illusion.
